    "The above review suggests that MH content is certainly present on the TikTok platform.",
    "The degree to which MH communication available on TikTok is evidence-based, however, remains an open question.",
    "Several studies offer anecdotal evidence of the prevalence of mental health misinformation on platforms like YouTube and Instagram [18] [19] [20].",
    "But, efforts to do the same on TikTok are limited in their substantive scope 21 and thereby represent an underdeveloped field of study.",
    "The extent to which MHCCs might be persuaded to promote EBMHC on the platform is also an open area of research."
